<br>
Art <br>
I loved the show,thanks for flaming out. I loved it when you guys got serious in Nam. Felt like singing and dancing, Rock N Rolling all over again.<br><br>
Just like I remembered on Hill 65. Sitting on top of the bunkerplaying the juice box, listening to the sounds watching as Charles dropped his mortars against our 11th Marines artillery. No contest, but a great show to watch. <br><br>
We used to take bets on how many rounds it would take before one of ours got a secondary explosion. Then we would all cheer and give you all a toast. You certainly did get a lot of secondary explosions yesterday. <br>
Its good to drop a load every once in a while, my wife says that's the reason I write. to let off some steam.<br><br>
Take care. your brother in arms, peace and war and in between.<br><br>

<p><code>-- -  (Sparrowhawk) </code><p>


